[00:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In this guide, we\'ll walk through how to use auto and manual multi-image inputs. Auto multi-image input is designed for capturing a single environment with full 360° coverage. [music] To get the best results, stand in one spot and take multiple photos while rotating around'

[00:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the space. You can upload up to eight images, and both landscape and portrait images are supported. It works best when the images overlap so the model has enough shared visual [music] information between shots. When the images overlap, the model can reconstruct the'

[00:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'environment cleanly without introducing holes or hallucinated areas. [music] This gives you consistent coverage in every direction and produces an environment that accurately reflects the original space. [music] Next, let\'s move to the manual'

[00:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'multi-image input. This option supports up to four images and allows you to manually define how different environments are arranged within a single scene. Each image is assigned to a specific viewing direction, front,'

[00:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'back, left, or right, giving you control over what appears in each direction as you navigate the environment. This makes it easy to combine multiple environments into one coherent scene while maintaining clear directional intent.'

[01:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Here you [music] can see how each environment has been mapped to it assigned direction. If any areas need refinement, they can be quickly expanded and adjusted. After doing so, you\'ll have a complete'

[01:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'environment with no visible unwanted spots.'
